SIMPLE: housekeeper
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Housekeeper
<hw>House"keep`er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One
who occupies a house with his family; a householder; the master or
mistress of a family.</def> <rj><au>Locke.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who does, or oversees, the work of keeping
house; <as>as, his wife is a good <ex>housekeeper</ex></as>; often, a
woman hired to superintend the servants of a household and manage the
ordinary domestic affairs.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>One who exercises hospitality, or has a plentiful
and hospitable household.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Sir H.
Wotton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>One who keeps or stays much at home.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>You are manifest <qex>housekeeper</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>A house dog.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Housekeeping</ent>⟦br⟧
